the only one that's been
losing sleep over this.

18:21.099 --> 18:24.568
Yeah, but he gets
to ask questions.
I gotta answer them.

18:24.569 --> 18:26.904
Guess that makes you the dad.

18:29.207 --> 18:31.675
Are you ok?
Yeah.

18:33.745 --> 18:35.412
What are you
thinking about?

18:35.413 --> 18:37.781
The car.

18:40.085 --> 18:41.118
Hot rod?

18:42.587 --> 18:47.725
A 1957 ford fairlane
500 skyliner.

18:47.726 --> 18:51.494
It was two-tone -
deep emerald green and ivory.

18:52.897 --> 18:56.366
Why are you
thinking about that?

18:56.367 --> 18:57.434
Uh...

18:57.435 --> 18:59.803
That was the...

18:59.804 --> 19:02.773
That was the car
that dad and my brothers,

19:02.774 --> 19:05.776
We used to goof around
with on saturdays.

19:05.777 --> 19:07.711
And, god, it was...

19:07.712 --> 19:10.380
It was a hardtop convertible.
Those are tough to get.
You can't find them.

19:10.381 --> 19:12.382
Boy, that was a great car.

19:12.383 --> 19:14.317
You know, and then,
you know, he died.

19:19.390 --> 19:21.691
Uncle harry took the car,
and he sold it.

19:21.692 --> 19:23.693
We never seen it again.

19:23.694 --> 19:27.231
And that was the best thing
I ever remember about my dad.

19:29.033 --> 19:31.101
Honey,

19:31.102 --> 19:34.504
Isn't that the perfect reason
for you to sign a will?

19:34.505 --> 19:37.941
Well, that would be
the perfect reason, sure.

19:37.942 --> 19:41.078
Then why don't you
sign it?

19:41.079 --> 19:43.747
Dad was, uh...

19:43.748 --> 19:47.651
Only three years older
than I am now when he died.

19:47.652 --> 19:50.954
And he had all boys,
and I have all boys.

19:50.955 --> 19:55.725
And he, you know, he built
a ford in the garage, and...

19:55.726 --> 19:57.261
I got a ford in the garage,

19:57.262 --> 19:59.729
And I don't want my kids
growing up without their dad,

19:59.730 --> 20:02.166
And I kinda figure
that if I sign that will,
it means I'm gonna die.

20:03.301 --> 20:06.036
But you know that's not true.

20:10.809 --> 20:13.710
Besides, there's...

20:13.711 --> 20:17.014
There's one big difference
between you and your father.

20:17.015 --> 20:18.282
What's that?

20:18.283 --> 20:20.250
His car worked.

20:24.622 --> 20:26.656
I miss my dad
an awful lot, honey.

20:26.657 --> 20:27.691
I know, I know.

20:34.665 --> 20:36.766
Wanna go upstairs
and go to bed?
All right.

20:36.767 --> 20:39.402
Gonna be awful tired
tomorrow.

20:39.403 --> 20:42.005
Can you carry mark up?
Sure.

20:42.006 --> 20:43.941
